</article><!-- #post-## -->

			
				
<article id="post-32302" class="post-32302 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-media category-politics">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 role="heading" aria-level="2" class="entry-title"><a href="https://u.osu.edu/mclc/2020/01/24/u-of-minnesota-student-jailed-in-china-over-tweets/" rel="bookmark">U of Minnesota student jailed in China over tweets</a></h2>
		
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<time class="entry-date published" datetime="2020-01-24T12:05:35-04:00">January 24, 2020</time><time class="updated" datetime="2020-01-24T12:06:27-04:00">January 24, 2020</time>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		<div class="entry-author-byline">
			by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://u.osu.edu/mclc/author/denton-2/" title="View all posts by denton.2@osu.edu" rel="author">denton.2@osu.edu</a></span> at <span class="posted-on"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2020-01-24T12:05:35-04:00">12:05pm</time><time class="updated" datetime="2020-01-24T12:06:27-04:00">January 24, 2020</time></span>		</div>
			</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Source: Axios (1/23/20)<br />
<a href="https://www.axios.com/china-arrests-university-minnesota-twitter-e495cf47-d895-4014-9ac8-8dc76aa6004d.html">University of Minnesota student jailed in China over tweets</a><br />
By <a href="https://www.axios.com/authors/baebrahimian">Bethany Allen-Ebrahimian</a></p>
<div style="width: 572px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="i-amphtml-fill-content i-amphtml-replaced-content" src="https://images.axios.com/5vYpFiHxX44xSl7Yxzqy84hZzds=/2020/01/23/1579739710638.jpg" alt="Images of a cartoon villain" width="562" height="419" /><p class="wp-caption-text">The images Luo allegedly posted.</p></div>
<p>A Chinese student at the University of Minnesota has been arrested in China and sentenced to six months in prison for tweets he posted while in the United States, according to a Chinese <a href="http://wenshu.court.gov.cn/website/wenshu/181107ANFZ0BXSK4/index.html?docId=27a654e725c040df9423ab2800a16a11" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-vars-click-url="http://wenshu.court.gov.cn/website/wenshu/181107ANFZ0BXSK4/index.html?docId=27a654e725c040df9423ab2800a16a11" data-vars-post-id="" data-vars-link-text="court document">court document</a> viewed by Axios. Some of the tweets contained images deemed to be unflattering portrayals of a &#8220;national leader.&#8221;</p>
<p><strong>Why it matters: </strong>The case represents a dramatic escalation of the Chinese government&#8217;s attempts to shut down free speech abroad and a global expansion of a <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/10/business/china-twitter-censorship-online.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-vars-click-url="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/10/business/china-twitter-censorship-online.html" data-vars-post-id="" data-vars-link-text="Chinese police campaign">Chinese police campaign</a> to track down Twitter users in China who posted content critical of the Chinese government.</p>
<p><strong>What&#8217;s happening: </strong>Sen. Ben Sasse (R-Neb.) <a href="https://www.fox9.com/news/u-s-senator-calls-for-release-of-university-of-minnesota-student-arrested-in-china" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-vars-click-url="https://www.fox9.com/news/u-s-senator-calls-for-release-of-university-of-minnesota-student-arrested-in-china" data-vars-post-id="" data-vars-link-text="called on China">called on China</a> to release the student. &#8220;This is what ruthless and paranoid totalitarianism looks like,&#8221; said Sasse. <a href="https://u.osu.edu/mclc/2020/01/24/u-of-minnesota-student-jailed-in-china-over-tweets/#more-32302" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
	<footer class="entry-meta">
								<span class="cat-links">
